  RELEVANCE: Connects structural barriers (paywalls) to citational injustice. Relevant to literature review methodology: if reviewers have differential access to literature based on institutional resources, resulting bibliographies will systematically exclude work behind paywalls that reviewers cannot access. The open access argument suggests citational justice requires attending to structural access issues, not just representational concerns. Brief piece but makes important structural point.

